org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulators

Interface MappedData<K,V,T extends MappedData<K,V,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - The key that can be used to retrieve values
    V - The value type
    T - The intended comparable extended type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<T>, DataManipulator<T>, DataSerializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BodyPartRotationalData, EnchantmentData, StatisticData, StoredEnchantmentData

    public interface MappedData<K,V,T extends MappedData<K,V,T>>
extends DataManipulator<T>
    Represents item data that is mapped by a specific key and value type definition. Examples of these include: EnchantmentData, StoredEnchantmentData, etc.

    • Method Detail

      • getKeys

        Set<K> getKeys()
        Gets all the mapped keys stored on the item stack.

        The returned set is an immutable one, only representing the mapped key values available on this MappedData. To modify the available mapped key values, use the provided methods in MappedData.

        Returns:
        All mapped key values stored to the item stack

      • asMap

        Map<K,V> asMap()
        Gets all the mapped keys and their values and the levels stored on the item stack.

        The returned map is an immutable one, only representing the mapped key values available on this MappedData. To modify the available mapped key values, use the provided methods in MappedData.

        Returns:
        An immutable map of all keys and their values

      • set

        DataTransactionResult set(K key,
                          V value)
        Sets the key with the desired value.

        This will perform any and all checks that the given key is compatible with the represented item, and that the value is within the bounds of key.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to set
        value - The value of the key
        Returns:
        The transaction result, if the keys and their respective values were added, rejected or replaced

      • setUnsafe

        void setUnsafe(K key,
               V value)
        Unsafely sets the key at the desired value.

        This does NOT perform any checks on the item or whether the value is within the standard bounds of key.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to add
        value - The value of the key to add
